This library is a derivative work built on several projects:

1. The CTLL compile-time LL(1) parser (include/ctll/) originates from
   the CTRE project, compile-time-regular-expressions, by Hana
   Dusikova (https://github.com/hanickadot/compile-time-regular-expressions),
   used here via the notre fork
   (https://github.com/alexios-angel/notre). CTRE and CTLL are
   licensed under the Apache License 2.0 with LLVM Exceptions; Hana
   Dusikova retains authorship of that code.

2. The constexpr containers (include/ctc/) are vendored from
   compile-time-containers
   (https://github.com/alexios-angel/compile-time-containers),
   MIT licensed. The MIT terms and copyright notice for those files
   are preserved in that project's LICENSE and apply to the
   include/ctc/ copies distributed here.

3. The LL(1) parse table include/ctpy/python.hpp is generated from
   include/ctpy/python.lark by Tablewright
   (https://github.com/alexios-angel/Tablewright), an open-source
   replacement for the closed-source desatomat tool used by upstream
   CTRE.

4. The Python language it interprets is defined by the Python Software
   Foundation (https://www.python.org). ctpy is an independent,
   from-scratch compile-time implementation of a subset of the
   language; it contains no CPython source code.

5. The architecture - a Tablewright-generated CTLL table driving
   type-stack semantic actions - is shared with the sibling projects
   compile-time-lark, compile-time-json, compile-time-json5,
   compile-time-yaml and compile-time-xml (github.com/alexios-angel).

